body:
Can you show the output of
```
brew cleanup --verbose --debug
```
?

As a workaround, you can set `HOMEBREW_NO_INSTALL_CLEANUP` to skip the cleanup step during install/upgrade. You can still do `brew cleanup <formulae>` to cleanup things that you did install with `brew` (e.g. `brew cleanup $(brew ls --formula)`).

Also, what's the output of
```
ls -la /usr/local/lib/dgagent
```
?
